SIMPLE: miserable
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Miserable
<hw>Mis"er*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>mis⟦eacute⟧rable</ets>, L. <ets>miserabilis</ets>, fr.
<ets>miserari</ets> to lament, pity, fr. <ets>miser</ets> wretched. See
<er>Miser</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Very unhappy; wretched; living in misery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What hopes delude thee, <qex>miserable</qex> man?</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Causing unhappiness or misery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What 's more <qex>miserable</qex> than discontent?</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Worthless; mean; despicable; <as>as, a
<ex>miserable</ex> fellow; a <ex>miserable</ex> dinner.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Miserable</qex> comforters are ye all.</q> <rj><qau>Job xvi.
2.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Avaricious; niggardly; miserly.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Hooker.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Abject; forlorn; pitiable; wretched.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Miserable</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Miserable
<hw>Mis"er*a*ble</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A miserable person.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Sterne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Miserableness</ent>⟦br⟧
